com.google.appinventor.client.youngandroid
Class CodeblocksManager

java.lang.Object
  com.google.appinventor.client.youngandroid.CodeblocksManager
All Implemented Interfaces:
ConnectivityListener
public class CodeblocksManager
extends Object
implements ConnectivityListener

CodeblocksManager manages the client's connection to the Codeblocks JavaWebStart process, and provides methods for communicating from the client to the YaHttpServer (the HTTP server running with codeblocks)

Author:
sharon@google.com (Sharon Perl)

startCodeblocks

public void startCodeblocks()
Startup codeblocks. If codeblocks is already running, this method does nothing.

The work to start codeblocks and create a connection is done asynchronously, and it may not have finished by the time the call returns.

When codeblocks is up and we are connected, we will tell it to load the source file corresponding to the current project/file at that time.

canCancelCodeblocks

public boolean canCancelCodeblocks()

cancelCodeblocks

public void cancelCodeblocks()
Requests that we try to cancel the codeblocks launch.

If the JNLP file for codeblocks has already been downloaded, we may not be able to cancel.
